flowRoot.flowPara: At each node, pick best discriminator from sample of random input features, with respect to bootstrapped sample of observations
To predict for new y, pass your features through all trees. Average the values in leaf nodes for a single prediction
Each tree uses a subset of rows, so the remainder (OOB: out-of-bag data), can be used to evaluate model performance as the forest is generated!
Similarly, use OOB to assess variable importance: permute one feature and compare the RMSE on OOB with that of unpermuted.
OK with extraneous variables and mixed inputs, captures non-linear relationships, classification or regression.
